# Commit Conventions

## Preferred workflow

Use the interactive prompt — do **not** hand-write commits unless the user asks:

```bash
npm run commit   # czg — pick type, scope, subject
```

Hooks run automatically: `lint-staged` (pre-commit), `commitlint` (commit-msg).

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body optional>
```

| Rule | Limit |
|------|-------|
| Subject | ≤ 100 chars (`subject-max-length`) |
| Body lines | ≤ 100 chars each (`body-max-line-length`) — **split long lines** |

## Types (release notes mapping)

| Type | Release section | When to use |
|------|-----------------|-------------|
| `feat` | ✨ New | User-facing feature |
| `fix`, `hotfix` | 🛠 Fixes | Bug fix |
| `docs` | 📚 Documentation | README, CONTRIBUTING |
| `ci`, `build` | 👷 CI | Workflows, build scripts |
| `ui` | 🧹 Improvements | Visual-only (also valid) |
| `i18n` | 🧹 Improvements | Locale strings |
| `chore`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `style` | 🧹 Improvements | Internal / maintenance |

**Do not** use `release:` for daily work — `npm run release` creates `chore(release): vX.Y.Z` automatically.

## Agent rules

- Before commit, ensure staged files pass `lint-staged` (prettier + oxlint on ts/vue/css).
- If commit-msg hook fails on body length, shorten or remove the body — do not use `--no-verify`.
- Match repo style: lowercase type, imperative subject, no trailing period on subject.
- UI/cross-platform fixes: prefer `fix(ui):` or `ui:` over generic `fix:` when accurate.

See `.cursor/skills/release/SKILL.md` for how commits become release notes.
